  "body": "Hi there,\r\n\r\nI've found two instances of hasher in trie not returning to the pool, both in `Prove` and `LeafProof`.\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/blob/b91766f/trie/proof.go#L68\r\nhttps://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/blob/b91766f/trie/iterator.go#L183\r\n\r\nMy understanding of pooled objects in Go are that they have to be returned to the pool see [returnHasherToPool(h *hasher)](https://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/blob/master/trie/hasher.go#L71) I'm most certainly sure that it applies in this case.",
